CopperLP Research Code

Version: 0.1.0
Status: Development snapshot
Last updated: 2026-07-23

This repository contains the SageMath research code accompanying our work on computing asymptotic bounds for the automated Coppersmith method via linear programming.

The repository includes:

- Algorithm_1.sage: implementation of Algorithm 1 for computing asymptotic coefficients and small-root bounds;
- CIHNP_CSURF.sage: CIHNP-CSURF experiments;
- MIHNP.sage: MIHNP experiments with different numbers of samples;
- ECHNP.sage: ECHNP experiments;
- LCG.sage: truncated linear congruential generator experiments;
- LIPH_POKE.sage: LIPH-POKE experiments.

Each script is executed independently. Its inputs or experimental parameters are configured manually near the beginning of the corresponding SageMath script.

The repository is provided as a research code archive. It is not an installable software package and does not provide an automated batch runner.

SageMath 10.8 or later is recommended. The optional msolve backend is disabled by default and is not required for running the scripts.
